Comment: kristin_sophia said "Someone's barking up the wrong tree. Normally I wouldn't make a post like this but I saw it as an opportunity to touch on a serious subject and problem in our society. And that is a little term I like to call slut shaming. A woman should NEVER feel ashamed or be called out about her sexuality or otherwise. Last I checked men don't go around calling each other out on what they do in the bedroom or outside, in fact, they are always on each other's teams and have each other's backs. (which is how women SHOULD be with each other but that's an entirely different rant) Woman ARE allowed to express themselves sexually and otherwise without being scrutinized by other men AND women. Slut shaming perpetuates rape culture and is detrimental to women because it contributes to the miseducation of sex and women's bodies, for both women AND men. Meaning, it is sending out the message that what a woman's body looks like or what she does or doesn't do with her OWN body is anyone's business, new flash, it's NOT. Secondly, it further objectifies women as seeing them as less than human, an object to be handled, examined and inspected much like the body of corpse. Well it's time to realize that women are very much human and more than just a body made for your personal viewing or gossiping pleasure regardless of how they dress, look or act. A woman is allowed to portray herself in any which way she pleases and pursue her own pleasure in spite of this pervasive double standard. It's 2015 people, there should be a clear handle on this by now. It is time to dismantle the system and standards that justifies and encourages violence against women by policing and denouncing female sexuality."

Comment: kristin_sophia said "Someone's barking up the wrong tree. Normally I wouldn't make a post like this but I saw it as an opportunity to touch on a serious subject and problem in our society. And that is a little term I like to call slut shaming. A woman should NEVER feel ashamed or be called out about her sexuality or otherwise. Last I checked men don't go around calling each other out on what they do in the bedroom or outside, in fact, they are always on each other's teams and have each other's backs when it comes to those matters. (which is how women SHOULD be with each other but that's an entirely different rant) Women ARE allowed to express themselves sexually and otherwise without being scrutinized by other men AND women. Slut shaming perpetuates rape culture and is detrimental to women because it contributes to the miseducation of sex and women's bodies, for both women AND men. Meaning, it is sending out the message that what a woman's body looks like or what she does or doesn't do with her OWN body is anyone's business, new flash, it is most certainly NOT. Secondly, it further objectifies women as seeing them as less than human, an object to be handled, examined and inspected much like the body of corpse. Well it's time to realize that women are very much alive and very much human and more than just a body made for your personal viewing or gossiping pleasure regardless of how they dress, look or act. A woman is allowed to portray herself in any which way she pleases and pursue her own pleasure in spite of this pervasive double standard. It is 2015 people, there should be a clear handle on this by now. It is time to dismantle the imposed system and standards that justifies and encourages violence against women by policing and denouncing female sexuality and self expression. #WakeUp #ProudtobeaWoman 👊💪"

(which is how women SHOULD be with each other but that's an entirely different rant) Women ARE allowed to express themselves sexually and otherwise without being scrutinized by other men AND women. Slut shaming perpetuates rape culture and is detrimental to women because it contributes to the miseducation of sex and women's bodies, for both women AND men. Meaning, it is sending out the message that what a woman's body looks like or what she does or doesn't do with her OWN body is anyone's business, new flash, it is most certainly NOT. Secondly, it further objectifies women as seeing them as less than human, an object to be handled, examined and inspected much like the body of corpse. Comment: yogiyanni_ said "Day 2 of #2ndSeries is the six fundamental standing Asanas of Ashtanga. In this video, I am demonstrating Padagusthasana, Padahastasana, and Utthita Trikonasana: 
1.) Padangusthasana: 3 vinyasas
2.) Padahastasana: 3 vinyasas
3.) Utthita Trikonasana A and B: 5 vinyasas
4.) Utthita Parsvakonasana A and B: 5 vinyasas
5.) Prasarita Padottanasana A, B, C and D: 4-5 vinyasas
6.) Parsvottanasana: 5 vinyasas.

1⃣ Padangusthasana:
~ Samasthiti ~
Jump your feet hip width apart. Fold forward and grab your big toes with your thumb, index and middle finger. Inhale, lift your head up straighten your arms.
Exhale, fold forward with your head between your knees and elbows out to the side. Hold for five breaths.
Inhale, head up and straighten your arms. Exhale.
2⃣ Padahastasana:
Place your hands under your feet, palms up and the tips of your fingers towards your heels. Inhale, lift your head up straighten your arms.
Exhale, fold forward with your head between your knees and elbows out to the side. Hold for five breaths.
Inhale, head up and straighten your arms. Exhale and release your hands from under your feet and put them on your hips. Inhale and come up to standing and jump your feet together back together.
3⃣ Utthita Trikonasana A and B:
~ Samasthiti ~
Inhale. Jump to your right, arms spread to the side.
Trikonasana on the right side. Turn your right foot out. Exhale, lean down and grab your big toe. Gaze up at your fingertips. Hold for five breaths.
Release your big toe inhale and come up. Parallel your feet and arms spread to the side.
Trikonasana on the left side. Turn your left foot out. Exhale, lean down and grab your big toe. Gaze up at your fingertips.  Hold for five breaths.
Release your big toe inhale and come up. Parallel your feet and spread your arms to the side. Begin Trikonasana B (without returning to Samasthiti)…
The vinyasa count for Trikonasana B begins at 2.

Check out @yogawithmii for the other three fundamental postures, and make sure that you tag me, @yogawithmii - @yogiiza  and @splurgejuicecafe ***And if your profile is on private to make sure that you mark it public so may see your posts, hashtag #2ndSeries - happy practicing!!"

En mi vida profesional yo vendo todo tipo de negocios y cada día veo mas y mas personas llegar a Miami de Venezuela mal informados y sin el conocimiento adecuado para empezar de nuevo aquí. 
Lamentablemente amigos o conocidos tienden a dar consejos sin saber de que están hablando, consecuentemente familias enteras llegan sin un plan y sin saber como funciona el sistema en los EU. Muchos de ellos terminan arruinados, enfermos y hasta muertos (caso verídico ocurrido la semana pasada aquí en el Doral) . Y la verdad sea dicha, sin necesidad. Por que si hubiesen tenido asesoría adecuada muy seguramente que tendrían mejor oportunidad de salir adelante y de asegurar el futuro de sus familias.
Yo les recomiendo se asesoren por Abogados reconocidos en leyes de inmigración, Contadores titulados y asesores financieros con experiencia demostrada. El dinero que ustedes gasten en una consulta con uno de estos profesionales les puede ahorrar muchísimos dolores de cabeza en el futuro. Sin un mapa no se llega a ningún lado. Comment: nationsrising said "Many studies have concluded that consumption of dairy products may be linked to cancer.

1. “Casein, which makes up 87% of cow’s milk protein, promoted all stages of the cancer process,” says Dr. T. Colin Campbell, author of the well-regarded book, The China Study.

2. Several epidemiological studies have indicated a relationship between dairy consumption and breast cancer risk in pre-menopausal women (Outwater, 1997).” -Breast Cancer Fund.

3. “It appears that when individuals do not have the correct enzymes to metabolize many of the hormones naturally found in any type of cow’s milk, a glass of milk can flood the body with excess estrogen. This raises the risk of developing or accelerating the growth of existing breast cancer.” -Susan Wadia-Ells, Founding Director of
Knowbreastcancer.net.

4. “Some dairy products, such as whole milk and many types of cheese, have a relatively high saturated fat content, which may increase risk. Moreover, milk products may contain contaminants such as pesticides, which have carcinogenic potential, and growth factors such as insulin-like growth factor I, which have been shown to promote breast cancer cell growth.” -The American Journal of Clinical Nutrition.

5. “While scientists are hard at work searching for specific breast cancer-fighting compounds, the safest approach is to apply what we already know: Diets that are highest in a variety of plant foods and stay away from heavy oils, meat, and dairy products, help prevent a great many diseases.” -Dr. Neal Barnard, Physicians Committee for Responsible Medicine.

6. Some nutritionists confirm the doctors’ findings. One of them, Phil Richards, writes that “the connection between casein and cancer was so profound in rat experiments that the scientists could literally turn cancer growth on and off in the laboratory animals, like a light switch, simply by altering the level of casein protein in their diets.” Specifically, “consuming dairy products is linked to an increased risk for breast cancer as dairy products are high in fat, animal"

Well, here's some advice: Do not, we repeat, do NOT skip out on lunch at Rocco's Tacos - Welcome (multi-location). First off, order the guacamole. Comment: redpearlyoga said "Krista Shirley Ashtanga Workshop Weekend @redpearlyoga! March, 20-22, 2015. For more details on workshop schedule and registration, please visit redpearlyoga.com #namaste 
About Krista: 
Krista Shirley is a dedicated student and practitioner of traditional Ashtanga yoga.  She is an Authorized Level 2 teacher in the Ashtanga tradition of Sri K. Pattabhi Jois. She was introduced to this practice over ten years ago and immediately embraced it as a daily part of her life because she was magnetically drawn to the healing this practice provides. For the last eleven years Krista has rolled her mat out each day because it is such an intrinsic part of who she is. Ashtanga Yoga has given Krista health and wellness, comfort, stability, peace, mindfulness and an outlet to work on herself and help others. 
Krista began making yearly, long term, visits to Mysore, India in 2006 to study with the late Sri K. Pattabhi Jois, Guruji, in order to fully connect to this lineage and embrace and surrender to a teacher that could help facilitate her growth and provide a deep source of inspiration. Since Guruji’s passing in 2009 Krista continues to make the yearly pilgrimage to India to study with Guruji’s grandson R. Sharath Jois who has dedicated his life continuing the work of Guruji, ensuring this deeply rich lineage, this parampara, lives on in the name of Sri K. Pattabhi Jois."

Comment: rivkaover50 said "More snow tonight and tomorrow ,,missing Florida ! Www.heartsonparade.org  presented dozens of hearts painted by Florida artists and many were auctioned off on eBay to raise funds for Children's Home Society of Florida . I've always loved drawing hearts and I was one of those girls who doodled them all the time ! And I was thinking when I saw this exhibit about how many protective walls we put around our hearts .We walk through life as prisoners of heartbreak and struggle to break free. My message to you is practice small acts of courage in opening your heart ,such as calling a friend in need . It's hard for many to remain open hearted after someone disappoints you , but that's exactly when you have to let go of that person or the past ,forgive and just move on . I know it isn't easy , but trust me , after 52 years of going through many relationship traumas of all kinds in my day to day life , I know one thing : the heart is a miraculous organ and allows you to love again and open up again .. And again .,#love #heart #family #friends #pain #joy #heartache #heartbreak #breakup #boyfriend #girlfriend #friend #together #beauty #pretty #instagood #transformationtuesday #instamood"

Comment: rivkaover50 said "More snow tonight and tomorrow ,,missing Florida ! Www.heartsonparade.org  presented dozens of hearts painted by Florida artists and many were auctioned off on eBay to raise funds for Children's Home Society of Florida . I've always loved drawing hearts and I was one of those girls who doodled them all the time ! And I was thinking when I saw this exhibit about how many protective walls we put around our hearts .We walk through life as prisoners of heartbreak and struggle to break free. My message to you is practice small acts of courage in opening your heart ,such as calling a friend in need . It's hard for many to remain open hearted after someone disappoints you , but that's exactly when you have to just LET GO of that person or the past ,forgive and just move on . I know it isn't easy , but trust me , after 52 years of going through many relationship traumas of all kinds in my day to day life , I know one thing : the heart is a miraculous organ and allows you to love again and open up again .. And again .,#love #heart #family #friends #pain #joy #heartache #heartbreak #breakup #boyfriend #girlfriend #friend #together #beauty #pretty #instagood #transformationtuesday #instamood"

Comment: inasaulsbery said "One of my favorite moments from @blackenterprise #BEWPS: @verniceflygirlarmour concluded her presentation and picked up a copy of her book and asked the crowd, "Who would like this book?" The crowd began to clap and cheer. She asked a second time and the crowd began to clap and cheer louder. Well, when she asked a third time, a light bulb went off in my head and I got up out of my seat and proceeded to walk to the stage. What she was really asking, wasn't really a question. (HELLO? Is this thing on?) She was really saying whomever wants this book, come and get it! She was telling us to engage at a different level. Well you know me...😁 I got her book and I didn't have to push anyone out of the way to get it. I was the only one who got up out of my seat to get it. 👏👏 👏 Maybe, it's that entrepreneurial spirit in me. 😉 #thinkdifferently #daretobeextraordinary #thestarfiregroup #teamdreambigger #gutsymoves #engage #clearedhot #vernicearmour #firstfemalefighterpilot #zerotobreakthrough #amazingarmour<---- I made that hashtag up, I think Vernice will start using it from now on. 😜 @oprah @oprahmagazine"

Comment: marco_in_la said "#TBT #Christmas #Tree #Worm //
#Wreck #Diving #FortLauderdale #Florida 01.16.2015
☆☆☆☆☆
The common name for these worms #ChristmasTreeWorm is derived from their appearance, not their habitat or diet. Each worm has two brightly colored crowns that protrude from its tube-like body. These Christmas tree-like crowns are composed of radioles, or hair-like appendages radiating from the worm’s central spine. These appendages are used for respiration and to catch dinner, which typically consists of microscopic plants, or phytoplankton, floating in the water. These worms are sedentary, meaning that once they find a place they like, they don’t move much. In fact, while the colorful crowns of these worms are visible, most of their bodies are anchored in burrows that they bore into live coral. When startled, Christmas tree worms rapidly retract into their burrows, hiding from would-be predators. Christmas tree worms come in a variety of bright colors. They aren’t very big, averaging about 1.5 inches in length. However, because of their distinctive shape, beauty, and color, these worms are easily spotted. They are some of the most widely recognized polycheates, or marine burrowing, segmented worms out there.
☆☆☆☆☆
#ExplorationUnknown #Bluewater #gopro #Scubapro #polarpro #goprooftheday #goprophotography_ #goprouniverse #goprohero #underwatervideo #uwphotographer #vitaminsea #amazing #ocean #creatures #peoplewhodofunstuff #realsaltlife #livethesaltylife #StaySalty #SaltLife #scubadivingmag"

Comment: marco_in_la said "#TBT #Christmas #Tree #Worm //
#Wreck #Diving #FortLauderdale #Florida 01.16.2015
☆☆☆☆☆
The common name for these worms #ChristmasTreeWorm is derived from their appearance, not their habitat or diet. Each worm has two brightly colored crowns that protrude from its tube-like body. These Christmas tree-like crowns are composed of radioles, or hair-like appendages radiating from the worm’s central spine. These appendages are used for respiration and to catch dinner, which typically consists of microscopic plants, or phytoplankton, floating in the water. These worms are sedentary, meaning that once they find a place they like, they don’t move much. In fact, while the colorful crowns of these worms are visible, most of their bodies are anchored in burrows that they bore into live coral. When startled, Christmas tree worms rapidly retract into their burrows, hiding from would-be predators. Christmas tree worms come in a variety of bright colors. They aren’t very big, averaging about 1.5 inches in length. However, because of their distinctive shape, beauty, and color, these worms are easily spotted. They are some of the most widely recognized polycheates, or marine burrowing, segmented worms out there.
☆☆☆☆☆
#ExplorationUnknown #Bluewater #gopro #Scubapro #polarpro #goprooftheday #goprophotography_ #goprouniverse #goprohero #underwatervideo #uwphotographer #vitaminsea #amazing #ocean #creatures #peoplewhodofunstuff #realsaltlife #livethesaltylife #StaySalty #SaltLife #scubadivingmag"

Comment: kellygreenyoga said "This is Eka Pada Galavasana (one legged sage pose) - named after a sage... But, also nicknamed #flyingpigeon because of its physical similarity. 
This is a high variation. This pose could also be practiced lower- but the hips are for sure off the elbows. (That's where most peeps get stuck). I find that hooking the front foot with the toes, flexing, and pushing down is the ticket to success. The more you push that leg down the more your hips will pop up making space around the hip and squaring then off. This automatically lifts the hips up. 
Try practicing your #oneleggedpigeon on the floor. Heel toe the front foot up to 90 degrees (or as close to that as you can get) and flex your toes into the floor. Place your hands on the floor and push the shin down. As you do feel your hips square and pop up off the floor. This is exactly what we wanna do! Cool right?! Learn more tips for you and your students at our next #empowermovement #advancedyogatraining this April 20-25! Or pick @paigeheldyoga and my brain in #costaricayoga at our #yogaretreat in May! Check it out! Www.theyogajoint.com #thetimeisnow peeps! #namaste"

On April 16, 2015, I am joining an exceptional group of nurses & respiratory therapists from my Memorial family on a mission trip to Kingston, Jamaica.  Together we will educate the healthcare staff there on all topics regarding neonatal care.  Our goal is to share our knowledge & help Jamaica reduce it's infant mortality rate, a Millennium Developmental Goal that they hope to someday meet.  God has blessed me with this opportunity & the skills I need to make a difference.  I am confident that our group will make a huge contribution to the healthcare team in Kingston to improve all aspects of neonatal care that they provide to their community.  I have created this GoFundMe account in hopes to help us fundraise the costs of the clinical & educational supplies that we will need to bring with us as well as to aid in the cost of our extra-baggage charges to transport everything, & hopefully a portion of our lodging costs for the 10-15 of us who have volunteered for this mission trip.  Please consider supporting us.  Even the smallest $1 donation will help us as each & every dollar counts.  Thank you so much & God Bless!

Comment: duduwernik said "O mais importante é estar EMBASADO e AMPARADO PELA CIÊNCIA !

Se um gosta de usar cinza, o outro de gosta de azul, se um usa calça, o outro bermuda.

É problema pessoal e intransferível de cada um !!! Não perder nunca o FOCO é o mais IMPORTANTE!
Estudo, atualização, teoria e prática de acordo com a necessidade, disponibilidade e capacidades de seus clientes, alunos, pacientes ou atletas ! 
Porém, esteja sempre amparado e alinhado com a CIÊNCIA !

A boa informação, acho eu ? 
Todos já sabem o caminho para encontrar !

É sempre bom estar em palestras, cursos, congressos e saber que estamos no caminho certo, independente da didática ou metodologia que está sendo apresentada ! 
Todos os caminhos CERTOS (estudos, artigos, metanálises, evidências científicas), estão levando para o mesmo lugar ! 
O que estou querendo dizer, e a Ciência comprova, a título de exemplo, aliás alguns exemplos entre os MUITOS outros que Existem: 
1- É que exercícios isolados, em GERAL, não oferecem nada que um multiarticular não ofereça. Nada o impede de fazer ou usar, exercícios isolados em seus treinos, ou com seus alunos. Como falei acima (gosta de cinza, não gosta de azul, problema seu! )
2- Treinos intensos GERALMENTE não são volumosos, saber quando usar e com quem usar é responsabilidade do  #ProfissionalDeEducaçãoFísica, esse sim tem que estar atualizado, saber a hora de treinar forte, treinar leve, controlar o volume, a intensidade, dentre outras variáveis (tempo de descanso, cargas, escolha dos exercícios).
3- Escolher, optar, selecionar, exercícios mutilarticulares pensando em preservar articulações e tendões é estratégico e inteligente SIM, mas se quer fazer monoarticular, fique a vontade, porém preste muita atenção na hora de prescrever e dosar. .

Enfim, o que você quiser fazer, FAÇA!
Tenho alunos que estão treinando comigo fazem 12 anos, renovando contrato anual de Personal, ou seja, monto e acompanho treinos para pessoas comuns, empresários, mães, pessoas que trabalham, estudam, enfrentam trânsito, tem vida social, comem arroz e feijão e também vão a restaurantes nos finais de semana, comer um prato gourmet e tomar um bom vinho!
